    "narrative": "The Austin Waves\u2019 lineup today is headlined by the elite efficiency of **Jackson Merrill**, whose 75.27 score makes him our primary offensive engine. Facing Sean Burke (xERA 4.35), **Jackson Merrill** benefits from a massive platoon advantage and a favorable delivery cadence from the opposition, which creates a high-probability environment for stolen bases\u2014a critical asset for our 5x5 Roto standing. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** (70.65) and **Drake Baldwin** (67.34) anchor the core, with **Kyle Tucker** taking advantage of McGreevy\u2019s mediocre xERA and **Drake Baldwin** projecting well in the #2 hole, provided he maintains his projected lineup spot against the left-handed Brennan Bernardino.\n\nWhile several players sit near the 60-point threshold, the most difficult choice involved **Coby Mayo**. He finished with a respectable 52.17 score\u2014boosted by his ability to exploit slow SP delivery for stolen base upside\u2014but was ultimately benched because our utility and middle-infield slots are currently occupied by higher-ceiling plays like **Gunnar Henderson** and **Marcell Ozuna**. Our strategy prioritizes the platoon-advantaged **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (61.13) against Prielipp, where a wind-out forecast at the park adds a layer of confidence to his power projections. We remain wary of **Josh Lowe** and **Dominic Smith**; both carry \"Lineup Pending\" status and face significant SP skill headwinds (specifically **Josh Lowe**'s -19% SP skill penalty), which could force late-inning adjustments if their projected batting orders shift downward.",
